    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-09-08T18:26:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-09-08T18:26:00-05:00" n="464"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">310.2/9–853: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss> and to the
                        Mission at the United Nations</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d464fn1">Drafted by <persName>Betty Gough</persName> of
                            <gloss target="#t_UNP1">UNP</gloss>; cleared by <persName
                            corresp="#p_BACONRE1">Ruth Bacon</persName> of <gloss target="#t_FE1"
                            >FE</gloss> and <persName corresp="#p_RAYNORGH1">Hayden
                            Raynor</persName> of <gloss target="#t_BNA1">BNA</gloss>; approved for
                        transmission by <persName corresp="#p_MURPHYRD1">Murphy</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi> (London)</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-09-08T19:26:00-04:00"
                            >September 8, 1953—7:26 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1272 (London) and 99 (New York). As indicated <gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> 1235, <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> is required under
                    new rule 2 fix closing date at outset session and we will actively support
                    establishment date at around mid-December. Any proposal change this decision
                    later in session would in our view constitute reconsideration and thus require
                    two-thirds vote for adoption. US would vigorously oppose reconsideration and
                    with support <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> feel confident our view would
                    prevail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
